Mark Twain </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mightyk>MightyK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#3333ff>(5/13/03 12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: $$$$$</span><hr size=1> Perhaps a voucher the women take to the doctor or clinic that participates in the program would work. A voucher showing that she has talked to and decided to go with a more long term type of BC - IUD or Norplant or something. <br>
<br>
Honestly though, I think after a certain number of babies born with drug addictions and yeah I think the women should be sterilized. TO me, repeated offenses like that would amount to child abuse akin to molestation and rape. BUT, as much as I think it should be done I would never support a law that would order it done. My worry would be once you let the government in where would it stop. <br>
<br>
Kim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> sweetpeas mommy</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#3333ff>(5/13/03 6:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  money</span><hr size=1> OKay, here's where I took that the woman got money...in the original post, it said, &quot; read an article about a woman who offers to pay for Drug addict’s serialization so they don’t have any more drug addicted babies. She either has them get their tubes tied or go on Norplant or another type of long term birth control. She also gives them money when it is completed.&quot;<br>
<br>
I figured the money for the sterilization would go straight to the doctor, but I read the last sentence as she was giving money straight to the woman as well. (Ie: I'll give you a 100 dollars if you go get fixed.) As I said, the sterilization itself doesn't bother me too much (so long as the government isn't ordering it) but giving the women money for it does because it seems like it may cure one symptom of the problem (bring drug addicted babies into the world so they can be neglected) and yet at the same time, it perpetuates the original problem (the drug addiction) by giving the woman money, which likely will buy more drugs.<br>
<br>
But maybe I read it wrong???<br>
<br>
KA <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=powertotherae>Powertotherae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Satan's Lil' Minion</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#3333ff>(5/13/03 8:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=202.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re:Direct Quotes From the Article</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>In its five years, the organization has paid close to 1,000 women $200 each for getting sterilized or going on long-term birth control<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
